text: The Holt School is a secondary school for girls in Wokingham, Berkshire, England. It has over 1200 girls from ages 11-18. Boys are admitted to the sixth form. The school was founded in the 1930s. It is a specialized language and science college. It is in the top 200 highest achieving schools in GCSE, AS and A level exam results. Ofsted judged the school to be 'outstanding' and the sixth form to be 'good'. In 2013 88.3% of students got 5 A*-Cs in their GCSEs.http://www.holtschool.co.uk/uploads/Academic/Performance_Data/Yr_11_Analysis_2013_final.pdf ==References== Category:1930s establishments in England Category:Berkshire Category:Schools in England
